## ğŸ§® Functions

The `Functions` class contains advanced numerical algorithms and special functions.

### Implemented Functions

- Square root (Halleyâ€™s method)
- Cube root (Newtonâ€“Raphson)
- Factorial (integer & real)
- Gamma function (Lanczos approximation)
- Arithmeticâ€“Geometric Mean (AGM)
- Riemann Zeta function (Î¶)
- Dirichlet Beta function (Î²)

### Square Root (Halleyâ€™s Method)

```python
from AxiomX import Functions

f = Functions()
print(f.sqrt(2))
```

### Gamma Function

Extends factorials to real numbers:

```python
f.gamma(5.5)
```

